ads dominate at 58% of cost — expected for long conversation sessions where context accumulates.\n\n#### Cost by Phase\n\n| Phase | Calls | Cost | % |\n|-------|-------|------|---|\n| verify | 3,712 | $463.66 | 53.4% |\n| orchestrator | 870 | $191.88 | 22.1% |\n| retro | 749 | $102.52 | 11.8% |\n| code-review | 376 | $43.15 | 5.0% |\n| create-story | 348 | $37.05 | 4.3% |\n| dev-story | 271 | $30.07 | 3.5% |\n\nVerification is 53% of total spend. Partly justified (thorough verification catches bugs) and partly inflated by repeated no-op sessions that still run verification logic.\n\n#### Waste Estimate\n\nThe \"unknown\" cost bucket is $223.63 (25.8% of total). Combined with repeated state-fix sessions (~35 no-op loops), estimated wasted spend is $150-250 on sessions that accomplished nothing beyond re-fixing Ralph's state corruption.\n\n### 4. What Went Well\n\n- **Sprint complete:** All 74 stories across 17 epics are done. Zero stories failed verification.\n- **Code review caught real bugs:** 1 HIGH and 9 MEDIUM issues found and fixed across 4 stories today.\n- **Coverage held:** 96.85% overall, well above the 90% target. All 158 files above 80% floor.\n- **Verification thoroughness:** 41/41 ACs passed across 4 stories (16-5 through 16-8). Test count increased to 4,020.\n- **No rework:** Zero stories were sent back for re-development.\n\n### 5. What Went Wrong\n\n- **Status sync gap:** Stories were verified and passing but not atomically marked as `done`. This created a gap where subsequent sessions had to re-discover completion and re-sync status.\n- **Ralph state corruption (ongoing):** The stale in-memory state bug has been running for 35+ sessions. Each loop overwrites the corrected state with stale data, requiring the next session to fix it again. Pure waste.\n- **Cost attribution gap:** 25.8% of total spend ($223.63) is unattributed (\"unknown\" bucket). Cannot analyze or optimize what you cannot measure.\n- **Redundant tool calls:** Multiple sessions logged npm test running twice where once would suffice. Small but adds up across hundreds of sessions.\n\n### 6. Lessons Learned\n\n1. **Status updates must be atomic with verification.** When a story passes verification, the state transition to `done` should happen in the same transaction. The current two-phase approach (verify in one session, sync status in the next) creates drift.\n2. **In-memory state requires monotonic versioning.** Ralph should never overwrite on-disk state with an older in-memory snapshot. A version counter or timestamp comparison would prevent 35 sessions of state corruption.\n3. **Sprint-complete should be a hard exit.** Once all stories are done, Ralph's main loop should detect this and stop spawning new sessions. No reason to continue looping.\n4. **Cost attribution must cover all API calls.** The 25.8% \"unknown\" bucket makes cost analysis unreliable. Every API call should be tagged with a phase and story.\n\n### 7. Action Items\n\n| Priority | Action | Status |\n|----------|--------|--------|\n| **P0** | Sprint is complete. Plan next sprint or close out. | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P0** | Fix Ralph state corruption — add compare-and-swap or monotonic version to state writes | CRITICAL — 35+ occurrences, estimated $150-250 waste |\n| **P0** | Add sprint-complete exit condition to Ralph's main loop | CRITICAL — stops wasting sessions |\n| **P1** | Make verification -> done status transition atomic | NEW |\n| **P1** | Attribute the \"unknown\" cost bucket ($223.63, 25.8%) | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P2** | Tier verification depth by story complexity | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P2** | Add subagent guideline: capture test output once, grep from capture | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P2** | Add bash version check or shellcheck enforcement for ralph scripts | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P3** | Clean up legacy terms (black.box references) in patches/templates | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P3** | Clean up `1-1-foo` phantom story references from tracking data | CARRY FORWARD |"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":381,"cache_read_input_tokens":27928,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":381,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_012SiJf5ZapKyCiffDen1TzT","session_id":"a2464115-d242-4836-ab98-c49ab4aac746","uuid":"e1f17f06-dd48-4440-980b-18e83f89face"}
