{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GrqG8DJDd6muWJWAYWkjrk","type":"tool_result","content":"  4200→\n  4201→### 6. Lessons Learned\n  4202→\n  4203→1. **Status transitions must be atomic with verification.** When a verification subagent produces ALL_PASS, the status update to `done` must happen in the same transaction — not left for a later session to discover and fix.\n  4204→2. **In-memory state must not overwrite on-disk state without merge.** Ralph's pattern of load-once, write-back-always caused 35+ sessions of state corruption. State writes should be compare-and-swap or at minimum check timestamps.\n  4205→3. **Verification cost needs structural reduction.** At $459/sprint (53% of total), verification should be tiered — lightweight checks for simple stories, full verification only for complex ones. Story 16-1 already introduced tier classification; it should be used to modulate verification depth.\n  4206→4. **Subagent guidelines should mandate single test capture.** Running `npm test` twice (once for full output, once filtered) wastes tokens. Capture once, parse from the capture.\n  4207→5. **Cost attribution must be complete.** The 25.9% \"unknown\" bucket makes optimization blind. Every API call should tag its story context.\n  4208→\n  4209→### 7. Action Items\n  4210→\n  4211→| Priority | Action | Status |\n  4212→|----------|--------|--------|\n  4213→| **P0** | Sprint is complete. Plan next sprint. | NEW |\n  4214→| **P1** | Fix Ralph state corruption — add compare-and-swap or monotonic version to state writes | CARRY FORWARD |\n  4215→| **P1** | Make verification → status transition atomic | CARRY FORWARD |\n  4216→| **P1** | Attribute the \"unknown\" cost bucket ($223.10, 25.9%) | CARRY FORWARD |\n  4217→| **P1** | Add sprint-complete exit condition to Ralph's main loop | CARRY FORWARD |\n  4218→| **P2** | Tier verification depth by story complexity (leverage 16-1 tier classification) | NEW |\n  4219→| **P2** | A